SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c03748875
Version: 4

HPSBMU02872 rev.4 - HP Service Manager Web Tier, Remote Disclosure of
Information, Cross Site Scripting (XSS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2013-10-30
Last Updated: 2013-12-11

Potential Security Impact: Remote disclosure of information, Cross Site
Scripting (XSS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP Service
Manager and ServiceCenter Web Tier running on Windows. The vulnerabilities
could be exploited resulting in remote disclosure of information and cross
site scripting (XSS).

References: CVE-2012-5222 (SSRT101185, Disclosure of Information),
CVE-2013-2321 (XSS)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

HP Service Manager Web Tier v7.11, v9.30, v9.31
HP ServiceCenter Web Tier v6.2.8

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2012-5222    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P)       7.5
CVE-2013-2321    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P)       7.5
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following software updates available to resolve the
vulnerabilities.

The updates can be downloaded from HP Software Support Online (SSO).

